messages.content: Hi! I’m new here, what’s the tldr non-eng?

"Bittensor is an open-source protocol that powers a decentralized, blockchain-based machine learning network. Machine learning models train collaboratively and are rewarded in TAO according to the informational value they offer the collective. TAO also grants external access, allowing users to extract information from the network while tuning its activities to their needs."
bittensor.com -- learn section for more.

I read that stuff, over my head but seems promising... 

I'm probably not the right audience, I get 'setup a validator and train ML with the compute on the chain and access some benefits there'.  But how does "collaborative shared knowledge work" from an applied standpoint?
Where otc
https://discord.gg/2buwQMjT
*NOT affiliated with bittensor

Collaborative in the sense that everyday people have financial incentive to contribute compute to a massive internet scale neural net.... that the driver (incentive) is the same as that which made BTC become the largest compute network by a long shot... Bittensor's a massive neural net trained by servers (miners) and rewards them according to how much they contribute to it.
